<text xml:lang="ta">
  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <p xml:id="PN204-intro">tiṇaiyum tuṟaiyum avai. valvilōriyaik kaṟaitiṉyāṉaiyār pāṭiyatu.
      </p>
      <p xml:lang="en">  
      </p>
    </div>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="PN204">
<l>īyeṉa viratta liḻintaṉ ṟataṉeti</l>
<l>rīyē ṉeṉṟa lataṉiṉu miḻintaṉṟu</l>
<l>koḷḷeṉak koṭutta luyarntaṉ ṟataṉetir</l>
<l>koḷḷē ṉeṉṟa lataṉiṉu muyarntaṉṟu</l>
<l>teṇṇīr parappi ṉimiḻtiraip peruṅkaṭa</l>
<l>luṇṇā rākupa nīrvēṭ ṭōrē</l>
<l>yāvu māvuñ ceṉṟuṇak kalaṅkic</l>
<l>cēṟoṭu paṭṭa ciṟumait tāyiṉu</l>
<l>muṇṇīr maruṅki ṉatarpala vākum</l>
<l>puḷḷum poḻutum paḻitta lallatai</l>
<l>yuḷḷic ceṉṟōrp paḻiyala rataṉāṟ</l>
<l>pulavēṉ vāḻiya rōri vicumpiṟ</l>
<l>karuvi vāṉam pōla</l>
<l>varaiyātu curakkum vaḷḷiyōy niṉṉē.</l>
</lg>
<lg xml:lang="en">
<l corresp="1">Begging while saying “give” is lowly. Against that, </l>
<l corresp="2">saying “I won’t give” is more lowly than that. </l>
<l corresp="3">Giving while saying “take” is lofty. Against that, </l>
<l corresp="4">saying “I won’t take” is more lofty than that. </l>
<l corresp="6">Those who want water will not be ones who drink </l>
<l corresp="5">from the large sea with roaring waves, with an expanse of clear water. </l>
<l corresp="7">Even though it is stirred up when cows and deer go [and] drink, </l>
<l corresp="8">[and] of low quality as it occurs with mire, </l>
<l corresp="9">there are roads many at the side of drinking water. </l>
<l corresp="10">Apart from blaming bird [omens] and times, </l>
<l corresp="11">those who go, remembering, are not not blame. Therefore, </l>
<l>I won’t be vexed with you, may you prosper, Ōri, (12a-c+14d)</l>
<l corresp="14a-c">you generous one who gives without limit, </l>
<l corresp="12d-13">like the clouds in multitudes in the sky. </l>
</lg>
    </div>
